channel_sources:
- conda-forge
channel_targets:
- conda-forge main
docker_image:
- quay.io/condaforge/linux-anvil-x86_64:alma9
python_min:
- '3.10'

about.description:
Google Cloud DNS API provides methods that you can use to manage DNS for your applications. Google Cloud DNS is a scalable, reliable, and managed authoritative Domain Name System (DNS) service running on the same infrastructure as Google. It has low latency, high availability and is a cost-effective way to:: - make your applications and services available to your users. You can easily publish and manage millions of DNS zones and records using our API.
See the [quick start guide](https://googleapis.dev/python/dns/latest/index.html#quick-start).
about.summary: Google Cloud DNS API client library

name: google-cloud-dns
raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: google-cloud-dns
  version: 0.36.0

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/${{ name | replace('-', '_') }}-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4b0a4ec76c273901d48b1b73132c3fdcd31874850ca6424cd75e6d631ae3711e

build:
  number: 1
  noarch: python
  script: ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv --no-deps --no-build-isolation

requirements:
  host:
    - python ${{ python_min }}.*
    - pip
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python >=${{ python_min }}
    - google-cloud-core >=1.4.4,<3.0.0

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - google.cloud.client
        - google.cloud.dns
      python_version: ${{ python_min }}.*
  - requirements:
      run:
        - pip
        - python ${{ python_min }}.*
    script:
      - pip check

about:
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Google Cloud DNS API client library
  description: "Google Cloud DNS API provides methods that you can use to manage DNS for your applications. Google Cloud DNS is a scalable, reliable, and managed authoritative Domain Name System (DNS) service running on the same infrastructure as Google. It has low latency, high availability and is a cost-effective way to:: - make your applications and services available to your users. You can easily publish and manage millions of DNS zones and records using our API.\nSee the [quick start guide](https://googleapis.dev/python/dns/latest/index.html#quick-start)."
  homepage: https://github.com/googleapis/python-dns
  repository: https://github.com/googleapis/python-dns
  documentation: https://googleapis.dev/python/dns/latest/index.html

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xylar
    - parthea
